(task
  (name "findSecret")
  (signature ( (text str) ) str)
  (constraints
    (constraint "The input 'text' is a string.")
    (constraint "The last word in the text is the secret word.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Extract the last word from the input text.")
    (rule "Split the text into words based on whitespace.")
    (rule "Return the last element of the resulting list of words.")
    (return "Returns the last word in the input string. If the string is empty, return an empty string.")
  )
)
generated_code:
from typing import List, Optional, Dict, Set, Any
import heapq
import collections

class Solution:
    def findSecret(self, text: str) -> str:
        """
        Extracts the last word from the input text.

        Args:
            text: The input string.

        Returns:
            The last word in the input string. If the string is empty, return an empty string.
        """
        if not text:
            return ""
        words = text.split()
        return words[-1]
